 God said, "Let there be lights in the expanse of sky to
divide the day from the night; and let them be for signs, and for
seasons, and for days and years;

 By the sweat of your face will you eat bread until you
return to the ground, for out of it you were taken. For you are dust,
and to dust you shall return."

 He said,
"Blessed be Yahweh, the God of Shem;
Let Canaan be his servant.

 God enlarge Japheth,
Let him dwell in the tents of Shem;
Let Canaan be his servant."

 It happened, whenever the stronger of the flock
conceived, that Jacob laid the rods before the eyes of the flock in the
gutters, that they might conceive among the rods;

 Why did you flee secretly, and deceive me, and didn't
tell me, that I might have sent you away with mirth and with songs,
with tambourine and with harp;

 Then Jacob was greatly afraid and was
distressed: and he divided the people who were with him, and the
flocks, and the herds, and the camels, into two companies;

 Only on
this condition will we consent to you. If you will be as we are, that
every male of you be circumcised;

 They took their
flocks, their herds, their donkeys, that which was in the city, that
which was in the field;

 It happened, when Joseph came to his
brothers, that they stripped Joseph of his coat, the coat of many
colors that was on him;

 He restored the
chief butler to his butlership again, and he gave the cup into
Pharaoh's hand;

 and the plenty
will not be known in the land by reason of that famine which follows;
for it will be very grievous.

 Now therefore when I
come to your servant my father, and the boy is not with us; seeing that
his life is bound up in the boy's life;

 There I will nourish you;
for there are yet five years of famine; lest you come to poverty, you,
and your household, and all that you have."'

                        Israel lived in the land of Egypt, in the land of Goshen;
and they got themselves possessions therein, and were fruitful, and
multiplied exceedingly.

"Reuben, you are my firstborn, my might, and the beginning of my
     strength;
  The pre-eminence of dignity, and the pre-eminence of power.

Boiling over as water, you shall not have the pre-eminence;
  Because you went up to your father's bed;
  Then defiled it. He went up to my couch.

 My soul, don't come into their council;
   My glory, don't be united to their assembly;
For in their anger they killed a man,
   In their self-will they hamstrung an ox.

"Judah, your brothers will praise you:
  Your hand will be on the neck of your enemies;
  Your father's sons will bow down before you.

"Joseph is a fruitful bough,
  A fruitful bough by a spring;
  His branches run over the wall.
